# .claudeignore
# Files and directories that Claude should NOT read unless explicitly asked
# Similar to .gitignore but for AI context prioritization

# ============================================================================
# LOW PRIORITY - Don't read unless explicitly requested
# ============================================================================

# Test Files (unless debugging tests)
backend/tests/**
frontend-nextjs/e2e/**
**/__tests__/**
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx

# Build Artifacts
.next/**
__pycache__/**
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# Dependencies
node_modules/**
.venv/**
venv/**
env/**

# Logs and Databases
*.log
*.sqlite
*.db

# IDE and Editor Files
.vscode/**
.idea/**
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# Environment Files (contain secrets)
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.development

# Git Files
.git/**
.gitignore

# Historical Documentation (low priority)
docs/_PRIORITY_3_HISTORICAL/**
docs/SPRINT_*.md
docs/TODO_*.md
docs/CRITICAL_ANALYSIS_*.md
docs/EMPTY_HTML_FIX.md
docs/NEWSLETTER_500_ERROR_FIX.md

# Temporary and Cache Files
*.tmp
*.cache
.cache/**
.pytest_cache/**
.mypy_cache/**
.tox/**

# Coverage Reports
htmlcov/**
.coverage
coverage.xml
*.cover

# Compiled Files
*.class
*.o
*.so
*.dylib
*.dll
*.exe

# Package Files
*.tar.gz
*.zip
*.rar

# Media Files (unless explicitly needed)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.svg
*.ico
*.mp4
*.mp3

# Lock Files (auto-generated)
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
poetry.lock
Pipfile.lock

# Migration Files (unless debugging migrations)
# Uncomment if migrations are stable and don't need frequent review
# backend/migrations/**

# Auto-generated API Docs
backend/docs/**

# Jupyter Notebooks (unless explicitly working on them)
*.ipynb
.ipynb_checkpoints/**

# Backup Files
*.bak
*.backup
*.old

# OS-specific Files
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ============================================================================
# NEVER READ - Security Risk
# ============================================================================

# Credentials and Secrets
**/credentials.json
**/secrets.yaml
**/secret.txt
**/*_secret*
**/*_key.pem
**/*_rsa
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/*.crt
**/*.p12

# ============================================================================
# EXCEPTIONS - Always read these even if they match patterns above
# ============================================================================

# Documentation is allowed
!CLAUDE.md
!README.md
!docs/_PRIORITY_1_CONTEXT/**
!docs/_PRIORITY_2_REFERENCE/**
!.claude/**

# Example environment files are allowed
!.env.example
!.env.template

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================

# This file helps Claude prioritize which files to read.
# Files matched by patterns above should NOT be read unless:
# 1. User explicitly asks to read them
# 2. Debugging requires reading them (e.g., test files when fixing tests)
# 3. They are in the exception list

# Priority Reading Order:
# 1. CLAUDE.md (always read first)
# 2. docs/_PRIORITY_1_CONTEXT/*.md (critical context)
# 3. .claude/instructions.md (reading strategy)
# 4. Relevant code files based on task
# 5. docs/_PRIORITY_2_REFERENCE/*.md (reference only)
# 6. Everything else only if explicitly needed

# To explicitly read an ignored file, user should say:
# "Read the file [path] even though it's in .claudeignore"
